 Cross-Site Scripting (UXSS): The Making of a Vulnerability</a></h4><p>What is Universal Cross-Site Scripting (UXSS)? Common cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks target websites or web applicat <a href=\"http://www.acunetix.com/blog/web-security-zone/universal-cross-site-scripting-uxss/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Read all article\">[...]</a></p></li><li><h4><a href=\"http://www.acunetix.com/blog/web-security-zone/communicating-management-web-security-part-3/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Posted on March 17, 2014 | 9:30 am\">Communicating with Management about Web Security, Part 3 – Getting and Keeping Your Message Out There</a></h4><p>We’ve all seen it. Apathy and disinterest are the name of the game with web security until a business deal is threaten <a href=\"http://www.acunetix.com/blog/web-security-zone/communicating-management-web-security-part-3/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Read all article\">[...]</a></p></li><li><h4><a href=\"http://www.acunetix.com/blog/web-security-zone/top-targets-blind-xss/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Posted on March 12, 2014 | 9:30 am\">Top Targets of Blind XSS</a></h4><p>Web-based security threats are a popular topic and you can easily find related information, including on cross-site scri <a href=\"http://www.acunetix.com/blog/web-security-zone/top-targets-blind-xss/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Read all article\">[...]</a></p></li></ul><div style=\"border-top: solid 1px #ccc; margin-top: 4px; padding: 2px 0;\"><p style=\"margin: 5px 0 0 0; padding: 0 0; line-height: normal; overflow: hidden;\"><a href=\"http://feeds.acunetix.com/acunetixwebapplicationsecurityblog\"\r\n                                style=\"float: left; display: block; width: 50%; text-align: right; margin-left: 30px;\r\n                                padding-right: 22px; background: url(http://ngo2.ru/kronung/wp-content/plugins/wp-security-scan/res/images/rss.png) no-repeat right center;\"\r\n                                target=\"_blank\">Follow us on RSS</a></p></d